events.description: Edict of Thessalonica: Emperor Theodosius I and his co-emperors Gratian and Valentinian II declare their wish that all Roman citizens convert to Nicene Christianity.
events.html: • 380 – Edict of Thessalonica: Emperor Theodosius I and his co-emperors Gratian and Valentinian II declare their wish that all Roman citizens convert to Nicene Christianity.[1]

events.description: The University of Constantinople is founded by Emperor Theodosius II at the urging of his wife Aelia Eudocia.
events.html: • 425 – The University of Constantinople is founded by Emperor Theodosius II at the urging of his wife Aelia Eudocia.[2]

events.description: Abaoji, chieftain of the Yila tribe, is named khagan of the Khitans.
events.html: • 907 – Abaoji, chieftain of the Yila tribe, is named khagan of the Khitans.[3]

events.description: The Treaty of Berwick is signed by England and the Lords of the Congregation of Scotland, establishing the terms under which English armed forces were to be permitted in Scotland in order to expel occupying French troops.
events.html: • 1560 – The Treaty of Berwick is signed by England and the Lords of the Congregation of Scotland, establishing the terms under which English armed forces were to be permitted in Scotland in order to expel occupying French troops.[4]

events.description: Henry IV is crowned King of France.
events.html: • 1594 – Henry IV is crowned King of France.[5]

events.description: Sweden and the Tsardom of Russia sign the Treaty of Stolbovo, ending the Ingrian War and shutting Russia out of the Baltic Sea.
events.html: • 1617 – Sweden and the Tsardom of Russia sign the Treaty of Stolbovo, ending the Ingrian War and shutting Russia out of the Baltic Sea.[6]

events.description: Yuan Chonghuan is appointed Governor of Liaodong, after leading the Chinese into a great victory against the Manchurians under Nurhaci.
events.html: • 1626 – Yuan Chonghuan is appointed Governor of Liaodong, after leading the Chinese into a great victory against the Manchurians under Nurhaci.[7]

events.description: American Revolutionary War: The Battle of Moore's Creek Bridge in North Carolina breaks up a Loyalist militia.
events.html: • 1776 – American Revolutionary War: The Battle of Moore's Creek Bridge in North Carolina breaks up a Loyalist militia.

events.description: American Revolutionary War: The House of Commons of Great Britain votes against further war in America.
events.html: • 1782 – American Revolutionary War: The House of Commons of Great Britain votes against further war in America.

entities.name: House of Commons of Great Britain

events.description: Pursuant to the District of Columbia Organic Act of 1801, Washington, D.C. is placed under the jurisdiction of the U.S. Congress.
events.html: • 1801 – Pursuant to the District of Columbia Organic Act of 1801, Washington, D.C. is placed under the jurisdiction of the U.S. Congress.

entities.name: District of Columbia Organic Act of 1801

events.description: Action of 27 February 1809: Captain Bernard Dubourdieu captures HMS Proserpine.
events.html: • 1809 – Action of 27 February 1809: Captain Bernard Dubourdieu captures HMS Proserpine.

events.description: Argentine War of Independence: Manuel Belgrano raises the Flag of Argentina in the city of Rosario for the first time.
events.html: • 1812 – Argentine War of Independence: Manuel Belgrano raises the Flag of Argentina in the city of Rosario for the first time.

events.description: Poet Lord Byron gives his first address as a member of the House of Lords, in defense of Luddite violence against Industrialism in his home county of Nottinghamshire.
events.html: • 1812 – Poet Lord Byron gives his first address as a member of the House of Lords, in defense of Luddite violence against Industrialism in his home county of Nottinghamshire.

events.description: The Dominican Republic gains independence from Haiti.
events.html: • 1844 – The Dominican Republic gains independence from Haiti.

events.description: Abraham Lincoln makes a speech at Cooper Union in the city of New York that is largely responsible for his election to the Presidency.
events.html: • 1860 – Abraham Lincoln makes a speech at Cooper Union in the city of New York that is largely responsible for his election to the Presidency.

events.description: American Civil War: The first Northern prisoners arrive at the Confederate prison at Andersonville, Georgia.
events.html: • 1864 – American Civil War: The first Northern prisoners arrive at the Confederate prison at Andersonville, Georgia.

events.description: The current flag of Japan is first adopted as the national flag for Japanese merchant ships.
events.html: • 1870 – The current flag of Japan is first adopted as the national flag for Japanese merchant ships.

events.description: First Boer War: The Battle of Majuba Hill takes place.
events.html: • 1881 – First Boer War: The Battle of Majuba Hill takes place.

events.description: King George I of Greece survives an assassination attempt.
events.html: • 1898 – King George I of Greece survives an assassination attempt.

events.description: Second Boer War: In South Africa, British military leaders receive an unconditional notice of surrender from Boer General Piet Cronjé at the Battle of Paardeberg.
events.html: • 1900 – Second Boer War: In South Africa, British military leaders receive an unconditional notice of surrender from Boer General Piet Cronjé at the Battle of Paardeberg.

events.description: The British Labour Party is founded.
events.html: • 1900 – The British Labour Party is founded.

events.description: Fußball-Club Bayern München is founded.
events.html: • 1900 – Fußball-Club Bayern München is founded.

events.description: Second Boer War: Australian soldiers Harry "Breaker" Morant and Peter Handcock are executed in Pretoria after being convicted of war crimes.
events.html: • 1902 – Second Boer War: Australian soldiers Harry "Breaker" Morant and Peter Handcock are executed in Pretoria after being convicted of war crimes.

events.description: Ocean liner SS Maloja strikes a mine near Dover and sinks with the loss of 155 lives.
events.html: • 1916 – Ocean liner SS Maloja strikes a mine near Dover and sinks with the loss of 155 lives.[8]

events.description: The International Working Union of Socialist Parties is founded in Vienna.
events.html: • 1921 – The International Working Union of Socialist Parties is founded in Vienna.

entities.name: International Working Union of Socialist Parties

events.description: A challenge to the Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution, allowing women the right to vote, is rebuffed by the Supreme Court of the United States in Leser v. Garnett.
events.html: • 1922 – A challenge to the Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution, allowing women the right to vote, is rebuffed by the Supreme Court of the United States in Leser v. Garnett.

entities.name: Nineteenth Amendment to the United States Constitution
Supreme Court of the United States

events.description: The Mäntsälä rebellion begins when members of the far-right Lapua Movement start shooting at the social democrats' event in Mäntsälä, Finland.
events.html: • 1932 – The Mäntsälä rebellion begins when members of the far-right Lapua Movement start shooting at the social democrats' event in Mäntsälä, Finland.[9]

events.description: Reichstag fire: Germany's parliament building in Berlin, the Reichstag, is set on fire; Marinus van der Lubbe, a young Dutch Communist claims responsibility.
events.html: • 1933 – Reichstag fire: Germany's parliament building in Berlin, the Reichstag, is set on fire; Marinus van der Lubbe, a young Dutch Communist claims responsibility.

events.description: United States labor law: The U.S. Supreme Court rules in NLRB v. Fansteel Metallurgical Corp. that the National Labor Relations Board has no authority to force an employer to rehire workers who engage in sit-down strikes.
events.html: • 1939 – United States labor law: The U.S. Supreme Court rules in NLRB v. Fansteel Metallurgical Corp. that the National Labor Relations Board has no authority to force an employer to rehire workers who engage in sit-down strikes.[10]

entities.name: Supreme Court of the United States

events.description: Martin Kamen and Sam Ruben discover carbon-14.
events.html: • 1940 – Martin Kamen and Sam Ruben discover carbon-14.

events.description: World War II: During the Battle of the Java Sea, an Allied strike force is defeated by a Japanese task force in the Java Sea in the Dutch East Indies.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: During the Battle of the Java Sea, an Allied strike force is defeated by a Japanese task force in the Java Sea in the Dutch East Indies.

events.description: The Smith Mine #3 in Bearcreek, Montana, explodes, killing 74 men.
events.html: • 1943 – The Smith Mine #3 in Bearcreek, Montana, explodes, killing 74 men.

events.description: The Holocaust: In Berlin, the Gestapo arrest 1,800 Jewish men with German wives, leading to the Rosenstrasse protest.
events.html: • 1943 – The Holocaust: In Berlin, the Gestapo arrest 1,800 Jewish men with German wives, leading to the Rosenstrasse protest.

events.description: The Twenty-second Amendment to the United States Constitution, limiting Presidents to two terms, is ratified.
events.html: • 1951 – The Twenty-second Amendment to the United States Constitution, limiting Presidents to two terms, is ratified.

entities.name: Twenty-second Amendment to the United States Constitution

events.description: The first congress of the Spanish Trade Union Organisation is inaugurated.
events.html: • 1961 – The first congress of the Spanish Trade Union Organisation is inaugurated.

events.description: Vietnam War: Two dissident Republic of Vietnam Air Force pilots bomb the Independence Palace in Saigon in a failed attempt to assassinate South Vietnam President Ngô Đình Diệm.
events.html: • 1962 – Vietnam War: Two dissident Republic of Vietnam Air Force pilots bomb the Independence Palace in Saigon in a failed attempt to assassinate South Vietnam President Ngô Đình Diệm.

events.description: The Dominican Republic receives its first democratically elected president, Juan Bosch, since the end of the dictatorship led by Rafael Trujillo.
events.html: • 1963 – The Dominican Republic receives its first democratically elected president, Juan Bosch, since the end of the dictatorship led by Rafael Trujillo.

events.description: The Government of Italy asks for help to keep the Leaning Tower of Pisa from toppling over.
events.html: • 1964 – The Government of Italy asks for help to keep the Leaning Tower of Pisa from toppling over.

events.description: Doctors in the first Dutch abortion clinic (the Mildredhuis in Arnhem) start performing artificially-induced abortions.
events.html: • 1971 – Doctors in the first Dutch abortion clinic (the Mildredhuis in Arnhem) start performing artificially-induced abortions.

events.description: The American Indian Movement occupies Wounded Knee in protest of the federal government.
events.html: • 1973 – The American Indian Movement occupies Wounded Knee in protest of the federal government.[11]

events.description: The former Spanish territory of Western Sahara, under the auspices of the Polisario Front declares independence as the Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic.
events.html: • 1976 – The former Spanish territory of Western Sahara, under the auspices of the Polisario Front declares independence as the Sahrawi Arab Democratic Republic.

events.description: Sumgait pogrom: The Armenian community in Sumgait, Azerbaijan is targeted in a violent pogrom.
events.html: • 1988 – Sumgait pogrom: The Armenian community in Sumgait, Azerbaijan is targeted in a violent pogrom.

events.description: Gulf War: U.S. President George H. W. Bush announces that "Kuwait is liberated".
events.html: • 1991 – Gulf War: U.S. President George H. W. Bush announces that "Kuwait is liberated".[12]

events.description: Loganair Flight 670A crashes while attempting to make a water landing in the Firth of Forth in Scotland.
events.html: • 2001 – Loganair Flight 670A crashes while attempting to make a water landing in the Firth of Forth in Scotland.[13]

events.description: Ryanair Flight 296 catches fire at London Stansted Airport causing minor injuries.
events.html: • 2002 – Ryanair Flight 296 catches fire at London Stansted Airport causing minor injuries.[14]

events.description: Godhra train burning: A Muslim mob torches a train returning from Ayodhya, killing 59 Hindu pilgrims.
events.html: • 2002 – Godhra train burning: A Muslim mob torches a train returning from Ayodhya, killing 59 Hindu pilgrims.[15][16]

events.description: A bombing of a SuperFerry by Abu Sayyaf in the Philippines' worst terrorist attack kills more than 100 passengers.
events.html: • 2004 – A bombing of a SuperFerry by Abu Sayyaf in the Philippines' worst terrorist attack kills more than 100 passengers.[17]

events.description: Shoko Asahara, the leader of the Japanese doomsday cult Aum Shinrikyo, is sentenced to death for masterminding the 1995 Tokyo subway sarin attack.
events.html: • 2004 – Shoko Asahara, the leader of the Japanese doomsday cult Aum Shinrikyo, is sentenced to death for masterminding the 1995 Tokyo subway sarin attack.[18]

events.description: Chinese stock bubble of 2007: The Shanghai Stock Exchange falls 9%, the largest daily fall in ten years, following speculation about a crackdown on illegal share offerings and trading, and fears about accelerating inflation.
events.html: • 2007 – Chinese stock bubble of 2007: The Shanghai Stock Exchange falls 9%, the largest daily fall in ten years, following speculation about a crackdown on illegal share offerings and trading, and fears about accelerating inflation.[19]

events.description: Jemaah Islamiyah terrorist Mas Selamat Kastari escapes from a detention center in Singapore, hiding in Johor, Malaysia until he was recaptured over a year later.
events.html: • 2008 – Jemaah Islamiyah terrorist Mas Selamat Kastari escapes from a detention center in Singapore, hiding in Johor, Malaysia until he was recaptured over a year later.[20][21]

events.description: An earthquake measuring 8.8 on the moment magnitude scale strikes central parts of Chile leaving over 500 victims, and thousands injured. The quake triggers a tsunami which strikes Hawaii shortly after.
events.html: • 2010 – An earthquake measuring 8.8 on the moment magnitude scale strikes central parts of Chile leaving over 500 victims, and thousands injured. The quake triggers a tsunami which strikes Hawaii shortly after.

events.description: A shooting takes place at a factory in Menznau, Switzerland, in which five people (including the perpetrator) are killed and five others injured.
events.html: • 2013 – A shooting takes place at a factory in Menznau, Switzerland, in which five people (including the perpetrator) are killed and five others injured.[22]

events.description: Russian politician Boris Nemtsov is assassinated in Moscow while out walking with his girlfriend.
events.html: • 2015 – Russian politician Boris Nemtsov is assassinated in Moscow while out walking with his girlfriend.[23]

events.description: Pakistan Air Force JF-17 Thunder downs Indian pilot Abhinandan Varthaman's Mig-21 in an aerial dogfight and captures him after conducting airstrikes in Jammu and Kashmir.
events.html: • 2019 – Pakistan Air Force JF-17 Thunder downs Indian pilot Abhinandan Varthaman's Mig-21 in an aerial dogfight and captures him after conducting airstrikes in Jammu and Kashmir.[24]
